# Python Coding Standards for PDFMark

## Code Style
- Use UTF-8 encoding with `# -*- coding: utf-8 -*-` header
- Follow PEP 8 style guidelines
- Use descriptive variable and function names
- Add comprehensive docstrings for all functions

## Import Organization
```python
# Standard library imports
import os
import re
from pathlib import Path

# Third-party imports
import fitz  # pymupdf
import pandas as pd
from fastapi import FastAPI, File, UploadFile

# Local imports (if any)
```

## Function Documentation
Always include docstrings with:
- Function purpose in Chinese and English
- Parameter descriptions
- Return value descriptions
- Usage examples when appropriate

## Error Handling
- Use try-except blocks for file operations
- Provide meaningful error messages
- Handle edge cases gracefully

## PDF Processing Best Practices
- Always close PDF documents after processing
- Use context managers when possible
- Validate file existence before processing
- Handle encoding issues for Chinese text
